341\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-tech/422733115/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-tech/422733115/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>") (pubDate nil "Tue, 12 Oct 2010 10:40:36 +0800") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142341") (dc:creator nil "MazingTech") (fs:srclink nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/155419/142341") (fs:srcfeed nil "http://www.yeeyan.org/feed/category/410") (fs:itemid nil "feedsky/yeeyan-tech/~8024233/422733115/5032246"))) ("碟状飞艇令“飞屋环游记”或成真" "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://www.popsci.com/technology/article/2010-10/disc-shaped-balloon-could-transport-whole-buildings-remote-areas\">Disc-Shaped Balloon Could Transport Whole Buildings To Remote Areas | Popular Science</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/76253\">colachoco</a></p><blockquote><p><img border=\"0\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.popsci.com/files/imagecache/article_image_large/articles/2a%20skypalaceabove.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"300\" /></p> <p>Skylifter's Disc Shaped Balloon Skylifter </p> </blockquote> <p><img border=\"0\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.popsci.com/files/imagecache/article_image_large/articles/2a%20skypalaceabove.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"300\" /></p> <p>Skylifter公司的碟状飞艇</p> <blockquote>Australian aeronautical firm Skylifter has come up with a better way to transport heavy equipment to remote areas that are beyond the reach of railways, roads and runways – a flying saucer.</blockquote> <p>澳大利亚航空公司Skylifter提出一种运输重型装备到铁路、公路和飞机无法到达的偏远山区的更好解决方案——飞碟。</p> <blockquote>This 150 meter-wide disc shaped balloon would be capable of carrying 150 tons, an increase of 700 percent from the maximum 20 tons able to be lifted by existing heavy transport helicopters. Its design provides for more stability – with its flatter profile, it acts less like a sail, making it less susceptible to winds during flights of up to 1240 miles. The disc also behaves as a parachute during descent, ensuring a gentle landing, while the low-hanging control pod keeps it from being too top-heavy.</blockquote> <p>这种碟状飞艇直径为150米，运载能力达到150吨，相比现在的重型运输直升机最大20吨的运载能力提升了7倍。它的设计能够提供更好的稳定性——更平坦的外形，但是其作用并不像帆，这样能够在最远1240英里的飞行中更好地减少风的影响。而且在降落的过程中，飞碟还能充当降落伞来保证平稳落地，而挂在下面的控制箱能够避免头重脚轻。</p> <blockquote>Skylifter has already built a miniature remote-control version of the disc, named Betty. At three meters across, Betty is capable of carrying slightly more than half a kilo, but her primary function is to show how the design functions. The firm plans to build a full-sized prototype of the balloon over the next three years. If all goes well, before long, Skylifter’s flying saucer could be delivering whole buildings to remote locations, or just acting as a flying hotel.</blockquote> <p>Skylifter已经制造了一个小型的遥控飞碟，并取名为贝蒂。直径3米的贝蒂载重能力略大于半公斤，但是她的主要目的是展示这个设计的功能。公司计划在接下来的三年里制造一架全尺寸的样机。如果一切顺利，不久后Skylifter的飞碟就把整座大楼运送到偏远地区，或者来一把“飞屋环游记”了。</p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/76253/142417#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/179337/140524?from=rss_related\">碟型气球可以将整栋建筑运送到遥远的地方</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/126492/94503?from=rss_related\">船用备件如何得到处理</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/pestwave/49274?from=rss_related\">运输应用：我们到位了吗？</a></p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/422733116/yeeyan-tech/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/76253/142417\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-tech/422733116/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-tech/422733116/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>" "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/76253/142417" (19635 50930) old 8 nil nil ((title nil "碟状飞艇令“飞屋环游记”或成真") (link nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/76253/142417") (created ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T02:24:50+00:00") (issued ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T02:24:50+00:00") (modified ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T02:24:50+00:00") (id ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142417") (author ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) (name nil "colachoco") (uri nil "http://space.yeeyan.org/u/76253")) (content ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom") (type . "html")) "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://www.popsci.com/technology/article/2010-10/disc-shaped-balloon-could-transport-whole-buildings-remote-areas\">Disc-Shaped Balloon Could Transport Whole Buildings To Remote Areas | Popular Science</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/76253\">colachoco</a></p><blockquote><p><img border=\"0\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.popsci.com/files/imagecache/article_image_large/articles/2a%20skypalaceabove.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"300\" /></p> <p>Skylifter's Disc Shaped Balloon Skylifter </p> </blockquote> <p><img border=\"0\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.popsci.com/files/imagecache/article_image_large/articles/2a%20skypalaceabove.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"300\" /></p> <p>Skylifter公司的碟状飞艇</p> <blockquote>Australian aeronautical firm Skylifter has come up with a better way to transport heavy equipment to remote areas that are beyond the reach of railways, roads and runways – a flying saucer.</blockquote> <p>澳大利亚航空公司Skylifter提出一种运输重型装备到铁路、公路和飞机无法到达的偏远山区的更好解决方案——飞碟。</p> <blockquote>This 150 meter-wide disc shaped balloon would be capable of carrying 150 tons, an increase of 700 percent from the maximum 20 tons able to be lifted by existing heavy transport helicopters. Its design provides for more stability – with its flatter profile, it acts less like a sail, making it less susceptible to winds during flights of up to 1240 miles. The disc also behaves as a parachute during descent, ensuring a gentle landing, while the low-hanging control pod keeps it from being too top-heavy.</blockquote> <p>这种碟状飞艇直径为150米，运载能力达到150吨，相比现在的重型运输直升机最大20吨的运载能力提升了7倍。它的设计能够提供更好的稳定性——更平坦的外形，但是其作用并不像帆，这样能够在最远1240英里的飞行中更好地减少风的影响。而且在降落的过程中，飞碟还能充当降落伞来保证平稳落地，而挂在下面的控制箱能够避免头重脚轻。</p> <blockquote>Skylifter has already built a miniature remote-control version of the disc, named Betty. At three meters across, Betty is capable of carrying slightly more than half a kilo, but her primary function is to show how the design functions. The firm plans to build a full-sized prototype of the balloon over the next three years. If all goes well, before long, Skylifter’s flying saucer could be delivering whole buildings to remote locations, or just acting as a flying hotel.</blockquote> <p>Skylifter已经制造了一个小型的遥控飞碟，并取名为贝蒂。直径3米的贝蒂载重能力略大于半公斤，但是她的主要目的是展示这个设计的功能。公司计划在接下来的三年里制造一架全尺寸的样机。如果一切顺利，不久后Skylifter的飞碟就把整座大楼运送到偏远地区，或者来一把“飞屋环游记”了。</p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/76253/142417#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/179337/140524?from=rss_related\">碟型气球可以将整栋建筑运送到遥远的地方</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/126492/94503?from=rss_related\">船用备件如何得到处理</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/pestwave/49274?from=rss_related\">运输应用：我们到位了吗？</a></p>") (content:encoded nil "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://www.popsci.com/technology/article/2010-10/disc-shaped-balloon-could-transport-whole-buildings-remote-areas\">Disc-Shaped Balloon Could Transport Whole Buildings To Remote Areas | Popular Science</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/76253\">colachoco</a></p><blockquote><p><img border=\"0\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.popsci.com/files/imagecache/article_image_large/articles/2a%20skypalaceabove.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"300\" /></p> <p>Skylifter's Disc Shaped Balloon Skylifter </p